Description:
"We’re in the decade that design tools have exploded with innovation. Especially when it comes to digital product design, collaboration between designers and developers has become way easier as we’re no longer stuck in one massive battleship called Adobe Suite, designing raster assets, having to create and manually save each icon on multiple resolutions, or even printing a website and filling the page with redlines and instructions for the developer to implement.

Sketch is one of these new tools that gives you the power, flexibility and speed you always wanted in a lightweight and easy-to-use package.

In this hands-on workshop, we will design (yes, actually design) an Android native app in Sketch, learning how to speed up our workflow, check out some really useful plugins and learn how to deliver our designs to our beloved developers."'}, {'date': {'start': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'role': 'Founder', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Subtract - Product Design Community & Meetup', 'logo': None, 'url': None}, 'cause': 'ARTS_AND_CULTURE', 'description': 'Official Sketch meetup in Greece until January 2018 (scope expanded after that) and a Slack community for Greek Designers (Web, Digital, Product)'}]
